-- Russia Stocks Drop for Second Day on Oil, Citigroup Downgrade
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2010-10-08T13:59:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/russia-stocks-drop-for-second-day-on-lower-oil-copper-zinc.html
Russian stocks fell for a second day
as crude and metals dropped and Citigroup Inc. downgraded its
recommendation on the country’s equities.  Oil producers OAO Gazprom Neft and OAO Lukoil slumped 1.3
percent. OAO Polyus Gold, the country’s biggest gold producer,
lost 1.6 percent, helping to push the Micex Index of 30 stocks
lower by 0.6 percent to 1,459.11 at 5:08 p.m. in Moscow. The
index has gained 0.4 percent this week.  Oil,  Russia ’s main export, retreated as much as 0.7 percent
to $81.11 a barrel in  New York . Copper, zinc and nickel declined
in  London . GMK  Norilsk Nickel , the world’s largest producer of
the metal, retreated 1.2 percent to 5,293.51 rubles.  Citigroup downgraded Russia to “neutral,” the U.S. bank
said in a report dated yesterday and e-mailed today. The Russian
economy is likely to expand 5 percent this year instead of a
previous projection of 6.1 percent, Citigroup said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
